deck: Nahuel is a Native American warrior who travels with Nidawi's protector. He saved the life of Drake Sinclair by sacrificing himself in combat.
description:
Origin

Nahuel's full origin is untold as of The Sixth Gun Issue #37. All that is known is that he has some kind of history with Nidawi that prevents him from being anything more then her protector.

Creation

Character Evolution

Nahuel was at one time in his life a peaceful man. There is an unknown reason that has yet to be explained of why Nahuel chose to become a hunter and warrior as Nidawi's protector.

Major Story Arcs

Ghost Dance

Becky Montcrief must enter the spirit world to cure herself of a sickness caused by the Sixth Gun. While in the spirit world, she is vulnerable to attacks by a coven of Skinwalkers hired by Missy Hume. Skinwalkers are a tribe that can enter the spirit world by entering a deep sleep.

In order to protect Becky, Nahuel travels with Drake's posse to hunt down the skinwalkers before they can find and kill Becky in the spirit world. When they reach the encampent, the Skinwalker coven summons Wolf Raptors summoned by Missy Hume's blood. Nahuel uses his superior athleticism to fight the Wolf Raptors as a distraction to keep them away from the rest of the posse.

Not The Bullet, But The Fall

Nahuel travels with the rest of the Sixth Gun posse to track and hunt down Missy Hume who still possesses the last of the Six. Unbeknownst to the posse, Missy Hume has already been slain by Griselda the Grey and given the demon gun to Jesup. Jesup is preparing dark forces for an attack to claim the other 5 guns from Drake Sinclair and Becky.

When Jesup attacks the town of Brimstone Nahuel is one of the few who is able to fight against him and his forces. Unfortunately Nahuel must sacrifice himself to allow Drake and Becky to escape from Jesup, he makes several killing strikes on Jesup but due to the powers of the Fifth Gun it prevents him from dying. Nahuel is killed after Jesup strikes him several times in the chest.

name: Nahuel

deck: An ally to Drake Sinclair and the current wielder of Screaming Crow's power. She serves as a human host to channel the spirit of Screaming Crow.
description:
Origin

Nidawi is the current wielder of Screaming Crow's shrunken head. These remains were given to her by Henri Fournier, who is a collector of occult artifacts of great power. Screaming Crow had the power to tame the Thunder Birds. Now Nidawi wields this power.

Creation

Character Evolution

Major Story Arcs

Ghost Dance

Becky Montcrief has mastered the Sixth Gun to a level that not even General Hume has performed. This power has caused a sickness to develop in Becky. In order to cure herself, she must enter the spirit world. While in the spirit world, Becky is vulnerable to Skinwalkers that were hired by Missy Hume. The Skinwalkers are a coven with the ability to enter the spirit world while their physical bodies are in a deep sleep.

Nidawi and her protector, Nahuel, accompany Gord Cantrell, Kirby Hale, and the mummy Asher Cobb to track down and defeat the Skinwalker coven before they track down and kill Becky in the spirit world.

Before leaving on this journey, Henri Fournier gives Nidawi the shrunken head of Screaming Crow to lend his power for the fight ahead.

When they finally track down the Skinwalker coven, Wolf Raptors are summoned with the blood of Missy Hume to attack the small posse. Nidawi uses her newly acquired powers to create a construct of pure lightning in the shape of a bow. The bow fires bolts of lightning that kill some of the Wolf Raptors. They are successful in stopping the coven from continuing their hunt of Becky in the Spirit World.

Not The Bullet, But The Fall

Nidawi and the small posse protecting the 5 demon guns of the set of six set off on a mission to track down and kill Missy Hume. Unbeknownst to the posse, Missy Hume has already been murdered by Griselda the Grey Witch. Griselda takes the demon gun from Missy and gives it to Jesup.

Jesup is building an army of dark forces to lead an assault on the posse, who have stopped in a small village.

Powers and Abilities

The remains of Screaming Crow grant her all of the power that Screaming Crow had in his past life. She has the power to summon lightning from the sky to strike her enemies. She can project electric attacks that arc from her body in all directions. She can create a bow construct made of pure lightning. She can fire lightning bolts from this bow from long distances. It is unknown if she is able to create other constructs besides the bow at this time. She has demonstrated the power to manipulate the Earth, by raising large chunks of stone from beneath the surface to crush her enemies.

deck: Uzu Sanageyama is a member of Honnouji Academy's Elite Four student council and the chairman of the Athletic Committee. His Three-Star Goku Uniform is the Blade Regalia .
description:
Origin

Creation

Uzu Sanageyama (猿投山 渦, Sanageyama Uzu) is a supporting character of the Kill la Kill anime series that was produced by Trigger. It's directed by Hiroyuki Imaishi and written by Kazuki Nakashima. The character design was done by Sushio.

A tie-in manga series illustrated by Ryou Akizuki began on October 4, 2013 in Kadokawa Shoten's Young Ace magazine.

Major Story Arcs

Powers & Abilities

Powers:

Heaven's eye: Also known as Clairvoyance, this ability centers around Sanageyama's eyes, and is the ability to see every potential move an opponent may make before it happens. By watching the muscles in the body twitch and contract, he can foresee your next move and compensate. This ability is lost when he has his eyes sewn shut and is replaced by the Authority of the Mind's Eye. It was however, regained with the re-opening of his eyes to battle Kiryuuin Ragyou

Authority of The Mind's Eye: This ability replaces the Heaven's Eye when Sanageyama has his eyes sewn shut. By losing his sight, his other senses are heightened and more than make up for this handicap. It is powerful enough to the extent that he can smell Ryuko's sweat from across the battlefield or cannot drink tea for fear of burning his tongue. It is unknown his control over this, as he was seemingly unaffected by Nonon's sonic blasts during her fight with Ryuko.

Techniques:

One Thousand Thrusts: By wielding multiple swords in both hands, he is able to brutally beat down an opponent.

Finishing move: Sword of the Mind's Mountain: by combining his hands together, he creates an enormous shinai blade. He never fully utilizes it though, as his uniform is destroyed by Nui Harime.

Weapons & Equipment

Uzu Sanageyama is shown to be a talented swordsman, and his Three-Star Goku Uniform, Blade Regalia, focuses on that. He uses a bamboo sword, as well as shinai in combat. He has three different Blade Regalias.

Three-Star Goku Uniform

Blade Regalia

Blade Regalia Mk-I: The original transformation of his uniform, this transformation resembles green kendo armor, however on a much larger scale. It allows bamboo swords, as well as shinai, to extend from the arms. In addition, it grants him superhuman speed, fast enough to keep up with Ryuko at Senketsu's full speed. In addition, it amplifies his secret tehnique, Heaven's eye. This suit is destroyed at his first defeat at the hands of Ryuko.

Blade Regalia Mk-II: The second uniform that Sanageyama receives after sewing his eyes shut in order to gain the forgiveness of Lady Satsuki. It is revamped and shows his resolve to overcome his weakness. It is destroyed by Nui Harime when the nexus fiber is torn.

Blade Regalia Mk-III: The final uniform that Sanageyama uses. This uniform is more white than than efore and has more spikes. His speed is dramatically increased over the previous two forms. At these speeds he can dodge nearly any attack, and is near-impossible to see.

Blade Regalia: Secret Unsealed (剣の装・奥義開眼, Suruzan no Sō Ōza Kaigan) is the ultimate and final form of the Blade Regalia Goku Uniform. Sanageyama is seen slicing through huge numbers of COVERS, and even firing a whirlwind of energy from his sword capable of destroying enemies without touching them. It should also be noted that he was the only character capable of tagging Ragyou with her attempting to prevent it.

deck: Nui Harime is the grand couturier of Revocs who serves Satsuki's mother, Ragyo; and she's the killer of Isshin Matoi. She uses the purple Scissor Blade as her weapon.
description:
Origin

Creation

Nui Harime (針目 縫, Harime Nui) is an antagonist of the Kill la Kill anime series that was produced by Trigger. It's directed by Hiroyuki Imaishi and written by Kazuki Nakashima. The character design was done by Sushio.

A tie-in manga series illustrated by Ryou Akizuki began on October 4, 2013 in Kadokawa Shoten's Young Ace magazine.

Major Story Arcs

Powers & Abilities

Swordsmanship

Nui has incredible skill in combat and swordsmanship. She has been able to defeat a transformed Goku Uniform and prove to be a formidable challenger to Ryuko in her kamui.

Weapons & Equipment

Bladed Tape Measure Whip

In flashbacks, Nui has been seen to use a retractable tape measure that has a collapsible serrated blade on one side. She uses this as a bladed whip that she swings and slices an enemy with. This was destroyed by Isshin.

Scissor Blade

Nui's weapon of choice is the purple Scissor Blade (片太刀バサミ, Kata tachi Basami) that was created by Isshin Matoi to counter the power of the Goku Uniforms.

She stole this half of the Rending Scissors after stabbing Isshin with it.

Life Fibers

Though Life Fibers (生命戦維, Seimei Seni) are normally used in the creation of clothing, Nui also uses them as both tools and weapons. She uses them to control life-like puppets and even slice clothing.
